pull.title: [Doc] Target protobuf 2.6 in OS X build notes.
pull.body:
Homebrew now installs Protobuf version 3 by default, which doesn't currently compile. So we should recommend installing Protobuf 2.6.x from the versions tap instead.

Should probably be backported to the 0.13 branch.

Discussion in #8741

events.message:
[Doc] Target protobuf 2.6 in OS X build notes.

Homebrew now installs Protobuf version 3 by default, which doesn't currently compile. Install Protobuf 2.6.x from the versions tap instead.

events.body: I'd add a brief note explaining the protobuf 2.6 requirement. Otherwise, it looks good to me.

utACK https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/8754/commits/b16a7f609fdb2efa9a8a1b82f09748b95b5ae4f6

For 0.14 I'd prefer that it just builds with protobuf 3.x (as this is going to pop up everywhere), but this is a good intermediate solution. Added the needs backport tag.
